I'm now focusing on a self-contained solution, and removing all unnecessary files. The main goal is to get this working. CORS errors are the root of my problem, so I am strictly updating `index.html` to not reference any other files. The `index.css` file will either be cleaned up or ignored. The goal is to make it runnable. The TypeScript is causing the CORS issue. I will ignore the CDN warning because I just need it to run!


**Structuring HTML for Success**

I'm now fully immersed in the meticulous process of structuring `index.html` for complete functionality. I'm focusing on the head section, ensuring all necessary CDNs – Tailwind, React/ReactDOM, Babel, Framer Motion, Lucide, and fonts – are correctly integrated. The inline Tailwind config and CSS are also being added. The body is simple; just a root `div`. The heavy lifting is in the script, where I'll simulate imports and ensure icons are accessible globally via `lucide`. I'll meticulously copy constants and context contents, and add the main logic.


